# Testing Standards (Playwright + Cucumber)

## Core Principles

- Playwright Test is the primary framework.
- Cucumber is used only for a small number of business-readable end-to-end flows.
- Do not convert the entire framework to Cucumber.
- Reuse existing helpers, fixtures, selectors, auth utilities, and page objects.
- Avoid duplicate test suites.

### Coverage Pyramid

- 70% API, contract, and session-injected tests
- 20% focused UI validation
- 10% true end-to-end business journeys

---

## Recommended Workflow

Write (TypeScript + POM)
→ Debug (Playwright UI Mode)
→ Push (Git PR)
→ Run in CI (4 shards in parallel)
→ Review failure trace
→ Merge only if all checks pass
→ Deploy

